# Cloudflare Worker Backend Rules

## Backend Scope

This backend handles:
- health checks
- backup reconcile / upload / download
- coach snapshot sync
- coach preferences
- profile insights
- sync chat
- async chat jobs
- async workout summary jobs

## Platform Rules

- This worker is built for Cloudflare Workers.
- Prefer declarative bindings in `wrangler.jsonc` over undocumented manual dashboard-only setup.
- Keep D1 / KV / R2 / Workflow bindings aligned with code and README.

## Contract Rules

- Worker request/response schema changes must be checked against iOS client code.
- If you change a schema, inspect:
  - `src/app.ts`
  - `src/schemas.ts`
  - iOS request models in `WorkoutApp/CoachFeature.swift` / `WorkoutApp/WorkoutSummaryFeature.swift`
- Do not broaden schema acceptance casually unless it is an intentional compatibility fix.

## Error Handling

- Keep structured logging.
- Preserve useful request diagnostics for validation failures.
- Prefer explicit typed request errors over generic failures.
- Do not hide upstream/model failures behind fake success paths.

## Workflows and Jobs

- Async chat and summary flows must preserve terminal job states.
- Inspect executor/workflow/state code together before changing job behavior.
- Wall time alone is not evidence of CPU bottleneck in workflows; inspect D1/KV/model/polling behavior separately.

## Validation

When editing backend code:
- run `npm run typecheck`
- run `npm test`
- if bindings/migrations/scripts change, update README and `wrangler.jsonc` consistently

## Safety

- Never log secrets or auth tokens.
- Avoid dumping full request payloads when they contain user state.
- Use route-specific safe diagnostics instead of raw body logs.

